# How we work in this repo

Source of truth is `docs/CONVENTIONS.md` — read it. This file is a thin adapter;
keep the real rules in one place.

@docs/CONVENTIONS.md

## The short version (enforced by review + tests)

1. **Plan before code** — affected files, interface changes, test list, blast radius.
2. **Layers** — protocol (`client.py`) / parsers (`activity.py`, byte-exact ports)
   / state+HTTP (`dashboard.py`) / pure engine (`sleep_engine.py`) /
   canvas UI (`index.dc.html`) / SQLite (`store.py`). Don't smear across layers.
3. **Data honesty** — absence is not a fact; minute-HR is the arbiter; show both
   numbers when they disagree.
4. **Verify against real data** — capture / DB / `/state` / screenshot, never "looks right".
5. **Watch is fragile** — minimise BT chatter; no polling during sleep; never
   restart the service mid-sleep-session.
6. **Tests are the guardrail** — behaviour change starts from a regression test;
   `python run_tests.py` must pass; `deploy.ps1` gates on it.

Before "done", run the Definition of Done checklist in `docs/CONVENTIONS.md` §7.
